Ceramic grocery bag wall hanging vessel 🤍 my goal at Em Holmie Ceramics is to re think objects function in order to create surprising interior spaces. This grocery bag adds dimension to my space and sits adjacent to my small apartment dining table. I chose some neutral floral for now, but already envisioning something vibrant next! Excited to share with you

Grocery bag vase, at home 🤍 when I got this piece out of the kiln this morning I rushed home just to put it on my dining table. I can never gauge how much I like or dislike my work until I see it in a home - where I envision it living and being used by others. Verdict is in and I love this one 🫡

Mini Bag Vases in 3 color-ways will be available next Tuesday August 15 on my website!

I made my first bag sculpture 4 years ago in grad school when I was feeling emotionally heavy. I thought to myself if I could just store these feelings somewhere to get through the next year I’d revisit them later when I had the capacity to. It was cheeky way to think about containment and the act of stashing away. Me and these lil bags, we’ve come such a long way!! 

.

My largest ceramic build yet! The piece is 25” tall and will become a table (assuming it survives the next two firings) 🙃 it was too heavy and scary to load from the top so I decided to take my kiln apart and rebuild it around the work. Everyone cross their fingers for me 🤞🏻 thank you to my pals @bykatelia and @studio_zedsie for the assist ❤️‍🔥

Introducing the Fragile hat 💔 Ceramics is fragile and durable, fragile and lasts forever, fragile and withstands heat. These dichotomies I witness everyday shape my perspective often. It reaffirms that I too am fragile and strong. I am thankful for this platform andd online visibility is overwhelming. I am excited for this holiday season andd it is full of greif. I dislike hyper capitalism andd I will be promoting product this entire month (lol). This hat, to me, is about holding many truths at once ❤️

Hats + limited holiday ornaments are available at emholmieceramics.com

Not to be dramatic but this lil bag changed my life 🙃 in the past 8 months we’ve made more than I can count, shipped to many states, and 5 different countries! Blows my mind every time I think about it. 

This will be the last week to pre order if you want one to arrive before the holidays! (This applies to domestic orders, I can’t guarantee anything international I’m sorry) I will be taking a slowed down approach in the new year to regroup, expand on the design, and hopefully streamline the process for shorter lead times. Thank you for your support :) 

.

Small Business Saturday 💌💌💌 thank you to everyone who has been on this journey with me! Supported me, encouraged me, and cried with me when I was overcharged for bubble wrap at the packing supply store. Running a small business really blurs the line between work and life - it’s all the same, all the time. Please!! buy from small businesses when you can and if you are able. It’s changes peoples lives, it’s changed mine
